        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 2:29PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 229 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles northwest of Squirrel Mountain Valley, or 31 miles southeast of
Porterville, moving northwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Glennville.
</description>
        <instruction>Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
